headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored a career-high 44 points and the severely short-handed Toronto Raptors scored a franchise-record 87 first-half points en route to a 135-115 blowout victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent scores career-high 44, Raptors rout Cavaliers 135-115

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Andre Drummond had 20 points and 11 rebounds, Dennis Schroder scored 19 points before he and Kyrie Irving were ejected in the third quarter and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Brooklyn Nets 126-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers pull away after ejections, rout Nets 126-101

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 27 points and nine rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 117-93 on Saturday night to pull even with Brooklyn for the Eastern Conference lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 27 points, 76ers beat Thunder 117-93

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 14 of his season-high 42 points in the fourth quarter and the Utah Jazz beat the Sacramento Kings 128-112 on Saturday night, extending their franchise-record home winning streak to 24 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Kings 128-112, extend home winning streak to 24

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 23 of his 38 points in the third quarter and the Golden State Warriors withstood another injury to rookie James Wiseman to beat the Houston Rockets 125-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 38 points, Warriors beat Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 27 points and the Phoenix Suns used a 44-point third quarter to rout the Washington Wizards 134-106 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 27 points, Suns rout Wizards 134-106

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Enes Kanter had 24 points and a franchise-record 30 rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers routed the Detroit Pistons 118-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kanter has 30 rebounds and Blazers beat Pistons 118-103
